The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Kuala Lumpur, June 13 (PTI): An Indian waiter in Malaysia was shot dead in a revenge attack near a restaurant in Kota Damansara on Friday night.           
	Dash, 30, was making his way to the restaurant workers dormitory near the eatery when a man shot him in the stomach and ran across the street to a waiting car that sped off. About 50 people were watching the live telecast of Fifa World Cup match in the restaurant when Dash was shot, police said.                   
	 Jammu (PTI): Fifty-one people, including 46 students, were injured in clashes between police and students of Baba Gulam Shah Badshah University at Rajouri on Sunday, police said. The students were protesting the mass failures in the under-graduate examination, allegedly because most of the questions were out of syllabus.                   
	 Ghaziabad (PTI): A bus driver saved three girl passengers from being kidnapped by an armed gang in the Uttar Pradesh town of Modinagar on Saturday night. The gang, travelling in the bus, tried to drag the girls out but the driver refused to stop the vehicle even after the kidnappers fired a shot. Other passengers then resisted the gang members, who fled as the bus ground to a halt.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Nalini Sriharan, who is serving a life sentence in the Rajiv Gandhi assassination case has accused prison authorities in Vellore of keeping her in isolation in violation of the prison manual.                   
	 Mumbai (PTI): Two teenage boys are feared to have drowned near Juhu beach on Sunday morning, police said. The boys have been identified as Alex Pandey, 15, and Rostren Decris, 16.                   
	 Ahmedabad (PTI): A woman allegedly shot herself dead with her husbands revolver at her home at a time all the family members were present there on Sunday. Dhruben Patni, 46, had cases of fraud registered against her, which could be the reason for her suicide, police said.                                                                                                                                              
